# Prompt Generator Overhaul — Walkthrough

## What Was Done

Rewired the Prompt Generator frontend to fully utilize the existing three-layer engine service per the PRD.

### Changes Made

#### [app.js](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/app.js)

**[generatePrompt()](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/app.js#179-226) — Fixed & Enhanced**
- Removed crashed `#generatorIntent` reference (element doesn't exist in HTML)
- Fixed property mapping: `genResult.finalPrompt` instead of broken `genResult.improvedPrompt`
- Passes the full generation result (intent, blueprint, v1, v2, scores, whyItWorks) to the renderer
- Added step-by-step progress indicator: `LAYER 1: INFERRING INTENT...` → `LAYER 2: BUILDING BLUEPRINT...` → `LAYER 3: GENERATING PROMPT...` → `ENGINE: COMPLETE`

**[renderGeneratorResults()](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/app.js#603-847) — Complete Rewrite (16 lines → 240 lines)**
Five premium sections:
1. **Final Prompt** — dark card with copy button and model name badge
2. **Auto-Score** — 5-dimension progress bars with overall score badge
3. **V1 → V2 Comparison** — side-by-side diff when auto-improvement triggers
4. **Intent & Blueprint Analysis** — split-view: inferred intent (task type, domain, format, control level) + prompt blueprint (role, task, constraints, target model)
5. **Why This Prompt Works** — collapsible educational explanation with emerald accents

#### [build-engine.js](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/build-engine.js) — No Changes
Engine bundle was rebuilt to pick up latest service code.

## Verification

Tested with prompt: *"Create a daily study plan for a college student balancing CS, gym, and meal prep"* targeting OpenAI GPT.

